                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1358b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GOA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Glazebrook</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Red Cross planning send about February 15 on United States collier about two tons
                    medical supplies for Jewish hospitals Jerusalem. Telegraph whether agent Jaffa
                    can arrange send small boat meet collier beyond mined area and land
                    supplies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
